Water Quality

Water quality refers to the chemical, physical, and biological characteristics of water based on the standards of its usage.

Key Factors Affecting Water Quality:

  • Dissolved oxygen
  • pH levels
  • Turbidity
  • Temperature
  • Nutrients (e.g., nitrates and phosphates)
  • Bacteria and other microorganisms

Importance:

Good water quality is essential for:

  • Human health and wellbeing
  • Ecosystem health
  • Agriculture and food production
  • Industrial processes

Monitoring and maintaining water quality is crucial for sustainable water resource management and environmental protection.
